1. To determine the approximate number of cereal bits in each design, we can divide the total number of cereal bits (63) by the number of designs (9). This gives us an average of about 7 cereal bits per design.

2. It's possible that Emily didn't use an equal number of cereal bits in each design. She might have used more or less depending on the complexity of the design or how she was feeling that morning.
